<paragraph blockId="62.[211,319,1132,1155]" box="[211,319,1132,1155]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis box="[211,319,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="325">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[211,1172,1171,1258]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325">
After 
<bibRefCitation author="Perrier R" box="[282,444,1171,1195]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325" refId="ref33915" refString="Perrier R. 1902. Holothuries. Expeditions scientifiques &quot; Travailleur &quot; et du &quot; Talisman &quot; pendant les anees 1880, 1882, 1883. Paris; p. 273 - 554." type="journal volume" year="1902">Perrier (1902)</bibRefCitation>
: no apparent papillae on dorsal surface. Lateroventral surface with big pedicels forming row. Mouth ventral, subterminal. One gonad, slender tubes, branched. One Polian vesicle. Respiratory trees well developed.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202464" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5202464" box="[211,1137,1662,1685]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202464/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="325" startId="62.[211,278,1662,1684]" targetBox="[211,1171,1316,1630]" targetPageId="62">
<paragraph blockId="62.[211,1137,1662,1685]" box="[211,1137,1662,1685]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325">
Figure 17. 
<taxonomicName authority="Perrier, 1898" authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1898" box="[327,684,1662,1685]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Mesothuriidae" genus="Zygothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Holothuriida" pageId="62" pageNumber="325" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="connectens">
<emphasis box="[327,551,1663,1685]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="325">Zygothuria connectens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perrier R" box="[557,684,1662,1684]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325" pagination="1664 - 1666" refId="ref33859" refString="Perrier R. 1898. Sur les Holothuries recueillies par le Travailleur et le Talisman. CR Acad Sci. 126: 1664 - 1666." type="journal article" year="1898">Perrier, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<bibRefCitation author="Perrier R" box="[745,875,1662,1684]" pageId="62" pageNumber="325" refId="ref33915" refString="Perrier R. 1902. Holothuries. Expeditions scientifiques &quot; Travailleur &quot; et du &quot; Talisman &quot; pendant les anees 1880, 1882, 1883. Paris; p. 273 - 554." type="journal volume" year="1902">Perrier, 1902</bibRefCitation>
, redrawn, scale unknown.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="63.[143,1104,167,255]" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">
Ossicles: disk with hole in centre, six to eight perimarginal holes and numerous holes in outer rings (
<figureCitation box="[379,493,199,223]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="62.[211,278,1662,1684]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,1316,1630]" captionTargetId="figure-167@62.[211,1171,1316,1630]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="Figure 17. Zygothuria connectens Perrier, 1898 from Perrier, 1902, redrawn, scale unknown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202464/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">Figure 17</figureCitation>
). Ossicles typically larger than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Theel" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[878,978,200,224]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Mesothuriidae" genus="Mesothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Holothuriida" pageId="63" pageNumber="326" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis box="[878,978,200,224]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">Z. lactea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Disk very irregular, spire high, ends in three (rarely four) smooth arms, curving upwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[143,241,302,326]" box="[143,241,302,326]" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis box="[143,241,302,326]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[143,1104,341,461]" pageId="63" pageNumber="326">
The description of the species was based on three individuals in poor condition, from off the Canaries at 
<quantity box="[353,434,373,397]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.975" pageId="63" pageNumber="326" unit="m" value="1975.0">1975 m</quantity>
and off the coast of Sahara, 
<quantity box="[750,900,373,397]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4215" metricValueMax="2.518" metricValueMin="2.325" pageId="63" pageNumber="326" unit="m" value="2421.5" valueMax="2518.0" valueMin="2325.0">2325–2518 m</quantity>
. The tables apparently have numerous holes in disk, and a few were stated to be four-rayed or even five-rayed.
</paragraph>
